Statistical Approach

We use Welchâs t-test, which is suitable for comparing the mean of two unpaired samples, with different variance. The null hypothesis H0 is that the mean main mass of the chanelled (Dir) surfaces is smaller than that of flat surfaces.

##        cell             p-value
## 1     hMSCs 0.00357752733107851
## 2 mioblasti 0.00568284130044572
## 3    shsy5y 0.00597024138889315

We can see that for hMSCs and shsy5y we can easily reject the null hypothesis; the p-value of the tests are way below 0.01. Unfortunately, we cannot say the same about mioblasti, where the p-value is 0.13. This could be an artifact of having only 4 flat instances for these cells.
